text:
by helping others....we help ourselves!

hello everyone!
all set for the valentine's week? 
what's your plan for making it special?

you can make it more special.
how?
here's an idea.

make it special for the less privileged and put a huge , beautiful and lovely smile on their faces. 
this valentine's let's donate to the less privileged. let's spread the *magic of love* 🤗

you can donate your part by google pay, paytm and phonepe too . remember, your amount of donation is not important but you taking initiative for a good cause is . small drops make large oceans so contribute your part ,we will make sure it reaches the right hands .'at last one good turn deserves another'😊
if you wish to offer something else please contact  on the numbers mentioned below .
common guys let's have a helping hand towards the future of our country .🙌 for further details : contact - yash(8308304111) or rohit(9923896846).
nisarga(8796009556)
[awaiting responses till 10th feb 2019]

도와주시고, 함께 해 주십시오"
.

text:
but wylie wasn’t just talking about fashion. he had recently been exposed to a new discipline: “information operations”, which ranks alongside land, sea, air and space in the us military’s doctrine of the “five-dimensional battle space”. his brief ranged across the scl group – the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as “mi6 for hire”, and i’d never quite understood it.
.
- it’s like dirty mi6 because you’re not constrained. there’s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it’s normal for a ‘market research company’ to amass data on domestic populations. and if you’re working in some country and there’s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that’s just a bonus.
.
when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it’s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‘oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.’
.
it was bannon who took this idea to the mercers: robert mercer – the co-ceo of the hedge fund renaissance technologies, who used his billions to pursue a rightwing agenda, donating to republican causes and supporting republican candidates – and his daughter rebekah.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
christopher wylie, the whistleblower who exposed the widespread misuse of data by his former employer, cambridge analytica, has revealed how the company “weaponised” the fashion industry in the run up to the 2016 us election, which he claims helped donald trump get elected.

speaking at the annual bof voices festival in oxfordshire, wylie revealed for the first time a matrix based on data collected by the firm which he claims can show how users’ preferences for particular brands on social media platforms – facebook, in particular – were then used to help target these same users with pro-trump messaging. he compared the misuse of fashion-based data as one of the campaign’s lesser reported “weapons of mass destruction”. - they [cambridge analytica] looked at actual people. how they engaged with certain brands was put into a funnel and helped build the algorithms, wylie explained. - when you look at personality traits, music and fashion are the most informative [tools] for predicting someone’s personality. a user’s predilection for a particular label gives, he said, a very clear indication of what reports often call “populist political signalling”. cambridge analytica, which was shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trump’s former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 – including cultural preferences such as fashion and music – to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political advertising.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

text:
cariño, perdóname, yo te quiero, lo hice sin querer. me pusiste muy nervioso y se me escapó la mano. di que te caíste, que fue un golpe accidental. no se volverá a repetir, lo prometo.

inocente ángel, que creía esas falsas promesas. ahora se cubre avergonzada los golpes físicos y mentales que su amor le propinó. ese miedo que incapacita distinguir las promesas reales de las mentiras de un cobarde que se crece cuando se pone violento.

huye, sal de ahí, te mereces ser feliz. si sucede una vez, ocurrirá más veces. no le creas.

ella @elyreross fotografía @javierfdelacruz él @victoralcazar_official maquillaje @siabeautycare .
.
.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

#repost @taranajaneen
• • • • •
i can’t express how proud i am of our new series of psas called ‘survivor stories’.
our team worked with the wonderful folks at @deutschinc and created this beautiful campaign in order to shift focus back where it belongs - on the people who actually said ‘me too.’ there are four in total. this one is close to my heart. so many men and boys have been left out of the conversation. we have to change that. 
please enjoy and feel free to share! 
#repost @metoomvmt @get_reposter 
we asked survivors to talk about their journeys to healing... and they agreed. we've taken care to limit graphic depictions. we are proud of the work, but please don't feel obligated to watch (or watch alone) as it may be too much. 
this is an anonymous survivors' story. many of us experience violence in our own communities and don’t find justice or healing in traditional ways. to anyone who has had the courage to speak up, and then let go... we see you. we hear you. we believe you. #metoo #survivorstories #youarenotalone #metoomvmt #webelieveyou #survivor #healingjustice #noshame

text:
today was one of those days where i felt beautiful, and everything around me came back to life. i now know what it's like to walk around without unnecessary emotional baggage, stuff that isn't my problem. and being with someone as an empath, you try to carry their burden like your own, and it does consume you. and when it's finally gone, you feel unusually empty, and it hurts because we associate absence with pain. but being on my own is the best thing that ever happened to me. knowing who you are, giving yourself the liberty to make mistakes and learning from them, is such a relief. .
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
rape culture
noun
1. a society or environment whose prevailing social attitudes have the effect of normalizing or trivializing sexual assault and abuse. 
that is the definition of rape culture. in much simpler words, it is treating rape as something that only happens because of where you were, who you were with, what time it was or what you were wearing. 
rape culture is denying the victim justice. in pakistan women are always burdened with the family’s honour, they’re told to not report the case because justice will never be served anyways. in other cases women deny themselves justice because theuy’re so many bad examples present in front of where police have been of no use, examples of women being harassed when they went to file a fir. 
rape culture is victim blaming. around the globe rape victims are usually asked questions like “what were you wearing?”, “who were you with?”, “did you say no?” and it is beyond my comprehension how you can try and find an excuse to justify the disgusting behaviour of a rapist. how you belittle their trauma, and their suffering. 
rape culture is constructing toxic stereotypes such as “boys will be boys, girls need to more careful.” this misinformed information only oversimplifies the problem. “manhood” is not defined as being dominant or sexually aggressive. young boys are told this from the beginning, their upbringing makes them think that aggressive behaviour is only natural, which is not the case. every time you let a boy get away with harassing a woman, you’re only teaching them that this behaviour is acceptable, you’re adding to the problem. 
rape culture is rape jokes. it’s as simple as saying “pakistan raped australia in the cricket match.” remember every time you joke about it, every time you share a “harmless” meme about it, a survivor flinches and cringes and suffers from traumatic flashbacks of the incident. rape culture is calling women like me oversensitive for taking offence at a rape joke, thereby degrading a woman’s trauma. 
rape culture is very real. please stop adding to it. let’s make this a better world a much better place to live in. 💗

text:
hundreds of junior high students in wonogiri, central java, have staged protests to demand that one of their teachers be sacked for alleged sexual assault of a female student, in the latest example of growing awareness of sexual harassment in indonesia.

the man, identified by the initials h.m., teaches english at smpn 1 slogohimo in wonogiri. he is accused of having touched the student in an inappropriate manner, according to a report by solopos.com.

the incident, which allegedly occurred in front of other students, resulted in protests over the weekend and on monday by hundreds of students who gathered outside their classrooms to demand his dismissal. 
photo by sigid kurniawan/antara

#metoo

text:
fragile, opulenta donna, matrice del paradiso
sei un granello di colpa
anche agli occhi di dio
malgrado le tue sante guerre
per l’emancipazione.
spaccarono la tua bellezza
e rimane uno scheletro d’amore
che però grida ancora vendetta
e soltanto tu riesci
ancora a piangere,
poi ti volgi e vedi ancora i tuoi figli,
poi ti volti e non sai ancora dire
e taci meravigliata
e allora diventi grande come la terra
e innalzi il tuo canto d’amore

text:
fragile, opulenta donna, matrice del paradiso
sei un granello di colpa
anche agli occhi di dio
malgrado le tue sante guerre
per l’emancipazione.
spaccarono la tua bellezza
e rimane uno scheletro d’amore
che però grida ancora vendetta
e soltanto tu riesci
ancora a piangere,
poi ti volgi e vedi ancora i tuoi figli,
poi ti volti e non sai ancora dire
e taci meravigliata
e allora diventi grande come la terra
e innalzi il tuo canto d’amore

text:
bringing this one back until you know it’s about you. until we all treat ourselves and each other like we know it’s about all of us....
here is what being a strong woman means to me: it means standing up for myself. it means that i am a fully-functioning human, one who is independent and able to do things for herself. it means that i have opinions and beliefs that i stand for, and that i do not settle for less. it doesn’t mean that i don’t ask for help. i do (often). asking for help doesn’t mean i’m weak, it means i’m able to acknowledge that i’m not a super woman, and that i’m going to need other people sometimes. being strong doesn’t mean that i close myself off from others and act like i’m better than them. (actually, i’m always striving to be better, live better, love better, which is about me rather than anyone else.) it doesn’t mean that i force my beliefs down other people’s throats, or judge them for how they think. it doesn’t mean that i’m ‘inevitably bitter or jaded’. in fact, a strong woman is a woman who loves herself and her world and is therefore positive, loving, and self-assured. to be a strong woman simply means that i am grounded and confident in who i am....#womanempowerment #zimbabwe #love #success #inspiration #positivevibes #metoo #womanpower #life #metoo #art #beauty #beautiful #feminist #feminism #inspirationalquotes #successfulwomen #motivation #slayqueen #blackgirlsrock #myblackisbeautiful #melaninpoppin #blackwomen #makeup #entrepreneur  #blackownedbusiness #fashionstyle #beautifulpeople  #bhfyp

text:
this is...tarana burke. 
tarana burke (born september 12, 1973) is a black civil rights activist from the bronx, new york who founded the me too movement. in 2006, burke began using the phrase "me too" to raise awareness of the pervasiveness of sexual abuse and assault in society, and the phrase developed into a broader movement, following the 2017 use of #metoo as a hashtag following the harvey weinstein sexual abuse allegations. time named burke, among a group of other prominent activists dubbed "the silence breakers", as the time person of the year for 2017. burke attends public speaking events across the country and is currently senior director at girls for gender equity in brooklyn. #blackhistorymonth #knowher #blackhistorymonth2019 #taranaburke

text:
📸📸📸
from ➡️ @nickassaur 
clarified jungle bird
.
1.5 oz. appleton 12 (@appletonestatecan)
3/4 oz. campari (@camparicanada)
1/2 oz. lime juice
1/2 oz. simple syrup (i used orgeat)
4 oz. pineapple juice
2 oz. whole milk (to clarify)
.
i hope you never get sick of seeing clarified cocktails because i never seem to get sick of making them. those who have previously enjoyed a jungle bird will know that the colour of this clarified version is drastically different than the usual orange/red hue of the original.
.
as with most clarified cocktails, this drink had a silky mouthfeel. the flavour of the campari was still present, but somehow drier, with most of the cocktail's sweetness coming from the orgeat and pineapple juice. the jungle bird has a special place in my heart as it is one of the first tiki cocktails that i learned to make. as such, it's always a joy to find new ways to riff on this tiki classic. stay tuned for my next post where i attempt to remake the jungle bird served at @aviarycocktails.

text_retweet:
reposted from @backto_muslimidentity -  perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks  pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.” kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. “menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, “tidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,” tukasnya.[]
name: itazaria

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.” kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. “menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, “tidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,” tukasnya.[]

하나 궁금한 건, 아직도 저 피해자들이 꽃뱀이라고 생각하는지. 아직도 저들의 이야기가 거짓이라고 믿는지.

text:
we tell ourselves that it is natural: their inability to control themselves. we teach self-control in other spheres of life. do not steal, no matter how nice that person's property is. discipline yourself to work hard and you will gain success.... but when it comes to a woman's body, we speak as if a man's genetics has never known self-control. "it is natural". is it because unlike stealing, society has shown us that breaking into a woman's body has little to no real-life consequence for the abuser? or that unlike hard work, controlling one's sexual urges does not seem to benefit the man? are our women's bodies, their sexual autonomy, inconsequential? what is it that makes us teach self-control until we are talking about a woman's body in relation to a man's desires? 
#artivist 
#poetwithapurpose 
#the_patriarchy_is_series
.
.
.
.
.

"it is natural". is it because unlike stealing, society has shown us that breaking into a woman's body has little to no real-life consequence for the abuser? or that unlike hard work, controlling one's sexual urges does not seem to benefit the man? are our women's bodies, their sexual autonomy, inconsequential? what is it that makes us teach self-control until we are talking about a woman's body in relation to a man's desires?

text: crumpets and tea. because i’m in england. ☕️🇬🇧don’t judge how much butter i use, it’s vegan. (keeping my diet balanced with gluten free oat milk and stevia). ok, so i’m posting a picture of my food, because i can’t take pictures of what i’ve been doing for the last 3 weeks. it’s far too precious and has taken me this long to even process what i’m experiencing. i’ve been hiding out in the uk volunteering with a non profit that safe houses women rescued from sex trafficking. for years my heart would pang every time i heard about this cause, and i knew one day i would eventually step into my calling to help vulnerable women. i didn’t think i was ready, healed enough, or had enough to offer, until one day last october when @jennygilpin came to speak at @c3.nyc women’s conference, with her message “just start.” it lit a fire in my heart, and i knew that if she could start an entire non profit with just a dream, the willingness, and the right heart, that i too could step out into my own mandate, which comes from proverbs 31:8 “speak out on behalf of the voiceless, and for the rights of all who are vulnerable.” a year ago i felt god nudge me to declare “women’s right’s activist” on my ig profile, even though all i had done at that point was attend the #metoo march in los angeles, and do a hell of a lot of work to heal my own heart and trauma. god speaks things into existence before they come. he spoke over me my victory when i still felt broken and couldn’t see the way out. three weeks into this mission, after wobbling heavily, nearly giving up, wondering how will i be able to handle the pain i feel from these women and children, i can say i am changed. my heart has been stretched beyond what i thought it was capable of holding, and i am stronger, steadier, and more on fire to live this mission as my purpose. meeting women face to face who have experienced horrors far greater than i ever will, and seeing how their lives have been transformed by the care of @cityhearts.global, has given me exactly the courage and strength that i needed to push forward and rise up. my heart is alive again. i am strong. i can handle her pain, and my own, in god’s strength alone.
name: Caitlin Rose

perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks  pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.” kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. “menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, “tidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,” tukasnya.[]

text:
justice for lai dai han enables political & community leaders to connect with the victims of sexual violence to understand their suffering first hand, and is creating public art as a permanent reminder of the plight of the lai dai han.

@rebeccahawkinssculpture the sculpture artist creating the 'mother and child' commemorative artwork, shared an update yesterday on her progress; "it is odd to think that no-one will ever see her from this position! still some work to do here but i have designed her eyes as small wells that will fill up and overflow down carefully crafted channels down the side of her face so that over time, the patina will show her crying."

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
🌈
جِــیمی رودمایر، نوجوان ۱۴ ساله در بوفالوی نیویورک زندگی و در مورد گرایش جنسی خود آزادانه با همه صحبت می‌کرد. در مدرسه بسیاری او را فعال اجتماعی و نوعی مبارز علیه همجنسگراستیزی می‌دانستند. شماری از آنها اما جــیمی را آزار می‌دادند و با کلمات اهانت‌آمیز جنسی او را مورد خطاب قرار می‌دادند.
.
 او پس از سال‌ها تحمل قلدری هم‌مدرسه‌ای‌ها، در ۱۸ سپتامبر سال ۲۰۱۱ دست به خودکشی زد. پدر جیمی خطاب به دو همکلاسی‌ای که بیش از دیگران پسرش را به خاطر گرایش جنسی‌اش آزار داده بودند گفت: «آن‌ها باید بدانند کلماتی که برای آن‌ها ممکن است جنبه شوخی و بازی داشته باشد، می تواند برای دیگران بسیار آزاردهنده باشد. این کلمات می‌تواند زندگی دیگران را نابود کند.»
.
جیمی به طور مداوم در وبلاگش در مورد آزاری که در مدرسه می دید، می‌نوشت. روز یکشنبه ۱۸ ماه سپتامبر، جیمی در فیس‌بوک خود آهنگی از لید گاگا به نام «ملکه» گذاشت که می‌گفت: «مرا فراموش نکنید زمانی که گریه‌کنان به دروازه بهشت می‌رسم.» .
بعد از آن در ساعت ۱:۳۰ نیمه شب روز یکشنبه، جیمی آخرین پست‌های خود را در تارنمای تامبلرش گذاشت. در یکی از پست‌ها نیز نوشت که خیلی دلش برای مادربزرگ‌اش، مادر مادرش که به تازگی فوت کرده تنگ شده است. در پست دیگرش از لیدی گاگا برای حمایتش از همجنسگرایان تشکر کرده بود. بعد از این دو پست، جیمی برای همیشه ساکت شد.
.
گروه کر همجنس‌گرایان لس‌آنجلس یک آهنگ برای جیمی اجرا کردند.
که مورد استقبال تماشاچیان قرار گرفت.
این آهنگ توسط ساشا ساکت اجرا شد، ساشا در ایران بزرگ شده و به قول خودش با جیمی همزاد پنداری می‌کند.
او هم تجربه خوبی از دبیرستان ندارد و آزار و اذیت‌های سایر هم مدرسه‌ای‌هایش را به یاد می‌آورد.
ساشا سال‌ها با افسردگی دست و پنجه نرم می‌کرد.
او بعد از شنیدن خبر مرگ جیمی این آهنگ را برای او سرود.
#قصه_های_خاموش 🏳‍🌈
#lgbt #metoo

text:
rape culture is fueled by misinformation and lack of proper education, and it's never too early to start teaching children about sexual abuse and the proper definition of consent. telling children that sexual assault is wrong is not enough. we need to make the issue of consent a more detailed and integral part of sex education. for young kids, it is about learning how to keep their bodies safe now, way before they even start thinking about being sexually active. if we are talking about teenagers, we are talking about sexual consent. sexual consent is not just a simple yes or no. consent can be given and then taken back. teaching kids about consent is not just one conversation. it is a lifelong discussion that starts when a child is young and it continues throughout their childhood and well into young adulthood. .

our infographic shows the data we currently have on child sexual abuse. .

if you're a survivor of sexual assault, kindly fill our data form through this link: https://shareanonymous.org/data-form/. and if you want to share your story, you can here: https://shareanonymous.org/share-your-story/. it is all anonymously.

text:
on stockholm furniture fair's first day, february 5, this year's first issue of form magazine will also be released. twelve designers from the fair share their views on sustainability, among them emma olbers, margrethe odgaard and alexander lervik. ▫️
in addition to several pages about stockholm furniture fair, form offers a return visit to kiruna's town hall, designed by arthur von schmalensee, a house that is now emptird and ready for the excavators and the demolition work. ylva frid and erik lefvander have visited the borderland between the new and old kiruna. ▫️
did you miss a #metoo call from the design world? in this issue of form magazine, susanne helgeson examines why it never happened, in the report "men who hate women". ▫️
in addition: interviews with norwegian agency anderssen & voll, design legend dieter rams, the swedish-nigerian fashion brand kenneth ize and the psychedelic icon zandra rhodes. ▫️
form 1/2019 – in stores and online on february 5. #formmagazine #stockholmfurniturefair

text:
perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks  pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.” kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. “menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, “tidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,” tukasnya.[] sumber:www.muslimahnews.com

text:
meet our founder!!!
tyde-courtney edwards is the founding director of ballet after dark, a classically trained ballerina, choreographer, art model and survivor of sexual assault. born and raised in baltimore city, she is a graduate of the baltimore school for the arts and has over 20 years of dance training and experience. trained in various styles of dance including classical and contemporary ballet, pointe, modern, lyrical, jazz, tap and hip-hop, she conceptualized ballet after dark after struggling with recovery following her sexual assault. tyde-courtney has trained with debbie allen dance academy, dance theatre of harlem, peabody conservatory, joffrey ballet, alvin ailey and other institutions while receiving training from local dance pioneers such as anton wilson, norma pera and stephanie powell. she currently resides in baltimore city.

be sure to visit the website today at www.balletafterdark.com! become a member and take advantage of new home workout and ballet tutorials being uploaded!

text:
i post this with all sincerity and any rude or idiotic comments will be removed.

the more i think about it the more angry i become. i read a post about the "me too" movement and the writer was assuming that since the women or girls didn't tell right away, they were lying. listen, i know people who still haven't told and won't tell until all the members of their family are dead and gone. do you know what it's like to live with those secrets? i know people who didn't tell when they should have because they were afraid of losing their jobs or being in the middle of a scandal. (have you been in those shoes?) i knew people who didn't tell in high school because they didn't want their father to kill some stupid man or they didn't want to somehow be blamed. (she asked for it) (did you see her skirt?) times have changed in the last 40 years and the workplace is, for the most part, not nearly as sexiest as it used to be. schools are trying to do a better job of teaching our children about inappropriate behavior. i am not saying that some women don't lie. all sexes and races lie. but not everyone is lying. so i want you to know that you are not alone. do not be afraid to seek counseling. do not be afraid to leave a dangerous situation. i stand with you. #metoo #bekind

text:
@eldiarioes la agencia de la ue de derechos fundamentales realizó en 2014 un estudio sobre violencia de género que reflejó que el 74% de las mujeres que tienen alta cualificación han sufrido acoso sexual a lo largo de su trayectoria. en el caso de las mujeres con formación media, el estudio revela que un 44% de las mujeres la ha sufrido, y en el 32% de todos esos casos señalaron como agresor a alguien de su entorno laboral, ya fuese un compañero de trabajo, un superior o un cliente. resulta demencial que en política, aquellos que blindan iniciativas contra la violencia de género no tengan protocolos internos contra el acoso sexual, tratándose de los partidos más votados en españa. en tiempos del #metoo o del #8m los representantes políticos que votamos como voces críticas eluden algunas de las funciones más básica; fomentar la discusión racional. por un lado, podemos ultima un protocolo contra el acoso sexual, el psoe está en proceso de negociar la actualización de su plan de igualdad de 2002 y ciudadanos asegura estar elaborando un plan de igualdad, aunque recalca que “nunca ha habido ninguna denuncia” y que  la igualdad se logra con políticas publicas que corrijan "los problemas estructurales y no con eslóganes". por su parte, el partido popular no cuenta con ningún plan ni protocolo específico contra el acoso sexual. los protocolos son necesarios porque consolidan el rechazo social a unas prácticas que atentan contra las mujeres; son necesarios porque ayudan a reducir los “vacíos legales” y la desprotección que hay para las víctimas de violencia machista. son necesarios porque para atajar la violencia machista hay que empezar por tu propia casa, así que  sres. y sras. de los partidos políticos y gobernantes  ya están tardando en terminar sus protocolos y den ejemplo a la ciudadanía.

text:
it's about time i tell ya'll what's been going on, instead of hiding in the dark hoping it all goes away.

if you've followed my page, about a year ago i started really accepting myself as someone who had schizophrenia. someone who for the rest of their life would be on antipsychotic medication. even though i was diagnosed with paranoid schizophrenia (from the old dsm) when i was a child, it didn't hit until then. that it didnt make sense, but the "doctors told me so", so i must really have schizophrenia. until, i was sitting in a meeting with psychiatrist, therapists, social worker, ect.. & three words would change my course of treatment, the way i viewed my life, & the way i viewed my trauma. "have we looked into the possibility that this is dissociative identity disorder?" three words i've never heard applied to me, and barely heard out of that context either. the next 20 minutes of the appointment it's like i left the room, and stopped listening. it was to much. over the course of 5 months, 4-5 hours of therapy a week, multiple psychiatrist appointments. i was diagnosed with it. its overwhelming, i haven't been on antipsychotics for almost a year, and its different. therapy is 100% different, and everything has changed. life hasn't gotten easier, but it feel like the muddy waters have become clear finally.

text:
s t r i p p e d 
a change is taking place....uprooted from the bottom through....plowed into pieces through each therapeutic experience.
this process leaves me vulnerable...my walls are being chiseled away...blasted away...broken through. i feel incredibly nude...naked....lynched of my dignity......stripped from sanity.

i felt so protected within the confines of my fortress... unafraid of the demons in my past... unafraid of those who had seared trauma into my soul.

the assault on my character left me with an invincible will girded in shields all over my mind...heart...body...soul.  in chains i placed on myself...thought it was a protection. 
isolation...is a prison yet i felt comfortable in the control it afforded me, you want me to join in arms now to free my soul? 
what freedom.... this is agony! 
you want to break my walls and surrender detachment out of my existence.

who will i be without her will protecting me... therapy will be the death of me... i'm suffocating from all the emotions flooding my system...numbness is thawing and i feel.

to feel is unbearable...the pain is rushing back like a million shards of glass cutting my spirit into kaleidoscope fissures throughout my mind.

migraines explode into memories on fire.

amidst the amnesia i was invincible...unware of the maladies lost in 
misery.

i'm stripped...this new me leaves me petrified.

the fear of shedding this skin which sheltered me is agonizing.

why face this pain...i was perfectly fine within the vortex of my forgotten past.

k. davae

text:
продолжаем знакомится с миром бабочек🦋
⠀
а вы знали что...? ⠀
▪️бабочки появились на планете более 200 млн лет назад – ученые обнаружили их останки, относящиеся к юрскому периоду.
⠀
▪️русское слово «бабочка» происходит от слова «бабка». сравнение этих чудесных насекомых со старухами обусловлено тем, что раньше бабочек считали душами умерших. в некоторых деревнях их и сейчас называют «бабушками» или «бабулями».
⠀
▪️совка агриппина – бабочка с самым большим размахом крыльев среди всех известных видов этих насекомых. он составляет до 28 см, а по некоторым данным – даже до 31 см.
⠀
▪️бабочки видят движущиеся объекты намного лучше, чем неподвижные.
⠀
▪️у бабочек, во время развития которых происходит генетическая мутация, одна половина тела может быть мужской, а другая – женской. иногда признаками другого пола обладают лишь отдельные участки тела бабочки – например, кусочек крыла самца имеет расцветку, характерную для самок.

text:
as i’ve read about case after case i’ve been thinking a lot recently about rape culture and the vilification of female survivors of sexual assault and what that shows about our current society. particularly the way the distrust in women’s sexual assault claims and the criticism they receive for speaking out, are directly correlated to the way society doesn’t respect or value women to the same extent as they respect or value men. as shown in so many cases, when it’s a woman’s word against a mans, more often than not, the mans word is taken as the truth. this is usually debunked if many women come out against the same man which was so prevalent in the #metoo movement. this is telling us that it takes multiple women and their words to have precedence over one single man, despite the fact that he. should. be. held. accountable. after. one. woman. bravely. alerts. the. world. to. his. criminality.  despite the bravery and strength it takes for a woman to come forward, and the abusive repercussions that stem from it (particularly in the public eye but also in places like russel group universities), women’s claims are so often belittled, distrusted or “swept under a rug.” i can’t stress enough the importance of sticking together and standing up for the words, testimony and protection of women. we also need to shame unacceptable behaviour and language from men to dismantle the rape culture that has formed.  if a friend or someone you know has said they have been sexually assaulted but doesn’t press criminal charges (which happens so often and for so many reasons) socially, we need to hold the men accountable in some way because those women are speaking the truth. i have known of boys who have continued with life and friendship groups as if nothing ever happened. this cannot continue.

believe survivors and believe women.

text:
mom guilt. partner guilt. friend guilt. these are three things that are crippling on our journeys to becoming our best selves.  we feel guilty for taking 30 minutes, 1 hour, or maybe even 2 so that we can set time aside for us to work on ourselves.  whether you workout at home or in a box/gym, you need to hear this.
.
.
there should be no guilt in taking time for yourself every day somehow. yes, every day. we need to move our bodies somehow if we want to stay healthy and be around for those memories with those we love.  there should be no guilt in taking time to do what is necessary to set routines to make this happen either.
.
.
you teach those around you how to take care of themselves when you set this example as well.  it is not easy, and as a mom i fight the mom guilt every day, but it’s necessary because how else will i teach my daughter how to fight back against the genes we have which predispose us to massive disease and obesity in our family? how else will i feel good in my skin and show others how to also?  there should be no guilt here.
.
.
the guilt comes at night when we’ve wasted another opportunity again to do something to better ourselves. it’s a daily choice and we must be the example.  i’m not perfect - so so far from it - but i will try to be the example for them, for you, and myself. .
.
.
at home, or in a box/gym, get moving this week. if you need help or guidance on where to start let me know. we have an amazing intro camp at @crossfit_i1uvit starting up again for those in town, and if you’re not then you’re welcome to be part of an online group with me with all the resources you need to work on yourself at home.  the choice is yours 💕

text: this is perhaps not the usual quote people illustrate, but i like it. here's why: jesus talks about the horror he faces and speaks of it "plainly". i do not celebrate that horror, but the way jesus was candid about it with his disciples. can i just say that in the church we very rarely speak candidly about horror? i am just as guilty about this as anyone. there's a streak of naivete and wishful thinking in the church that actively harms people, because it ignores good judgement, boundaries, and safety. there's a desire to pretend all is fine to maintain appearances. there's a desire to put on a brave face and not drag everyone down. i am so freed by the tradition of lament in the bible--where screaming in agony and prophetically speaking harsh words to the callous is held up as clarifying, courageous and necessary. we should learn from jesus' candor--not to celebrate the darkness but to let in the clarifying light of truth. #sermondoodle #mark8 #downer #horror #abuse #boundaries #safety #church #bodyofchrist #naivete #wishfulthinking #silenceisnotspiritual #metoo #churchtoo

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
aplicativo gratuito de financiamento coletivo converte pacotes de sms em dinheiro para projetos sociais sem fins lucrativos

com o objeto de conseguir recursos financeiros para projetos sociais ligados à cultura, entretenimento e empreendedorismo, o produtor e agitador cultural jony durap lança,o app nóis por nóis.

em parceria com uma  start up que desenvolve aplicativos diversos, jony  propõe uma nova forma de financiamento coletivo a projetos sociais de várias áreas, através da doação de pacotes de sms não utilizados pelos usuários de telefonia celular, cuja venda é revertida para as instituições.
a ideia inovadora não tem nenhum custo para os doadores, já que dificilmente utilizam o pacote de sms já embutido nos créditos inseridos. “além de gratuito, o aplicativo incentiva a prática da economia solidaria, fomentando várias ações dentro das comunidades carentes. quem baixa o app também terá descontos em produtos e concorre a vale-compras mensais”, explica jony du rap 
para  participarem, os interessados devem baixar o app nóis por nóis e escolher o projeto que desejam incentivar. 
conheça nosso site .www.noispornois.com.br

você sabia que quando coloca créditos no seu celular você automaticamente compra um pacote de sms que nem utiliza? pois é! pra gente ele é útil! e você pode fazer sua doação!
basta baixar o app nóis por nóis
porquê o futuro e colaborativo e solidário

text:
​​#историичитателей

недавно я смотрела программу о шурыгине и семенове. я знаю, что это все постановка, возможно, но! там был разговор, что она говорила ему "нет", но он продолжал свои действия.

я вспомнила себя в подростковом возрасте. когда мне было 13 лет я познакомилась с мужчиной старше на 11 лет. первый секс произошел через 6 месяцев. он, можно сказать, взял силой. я тоже была пьяной и говорила "нет". но мне нравились его действия. в следующие дни я продолжила с ним с удовольствием. далее было двое мужчин. старше уже на 20 лет, а потом третий на 30 лет старше. я встречалась сразу с тремя. и вела я себя отвратительно. пила водку с горла, курила по 2 пачки в день, орала матом, могла раздеться где угодно.

я хотела внимания. моя мать родила меня и бросила на бабушку. бабушка работала, а я шаталась по улицам. потом она умерла, и я стала жить с матерью и отчимом. отчим уходил в недельные запои. в доме постоянно тусовались его дружки - алкаши. отчим хватал меня за шею, за волосы, бил ремнем, ставил в угол, чтоб я часами стояла. иногда ставил на колени и на какую нибудь крупу. заставлял на вытянутых наверх руках держать какой нибудь груз. это очень неприятное ощущение. гонялся за мной по улицам. я постоянно хотела кушать. у меня не было одежды. все всегда было под замком. даже соль и сахар. у отчима была патологическая жадность.

что делала моя мать? лежала на диване с газетой. или спала. она была рада, что отчим ее не трогает. все доставалось мне. про мать как нибудь отдельный пост напишу. врагу не пожелаешь такое.

на фоне этого ада и унижений эти трое мужчин давали мне любовь, ласку, понимание, разговаривали со мной, советовали что-то, давали еду. ни один из них не относился ко мне плохо. тот, что на 30 лет старше даже с уважением относился, и говорил о любви.

в 18 лет все это закончилось. все как-то пошли своей дорогой. умер отчим. потом я вышла замуж за замечательного человека. он меня очень любит. у меня дочь 9 лет. я стараюсь, чтобы она даже рядом с такой юностью, как у меня, не проходила.
=====================

лежала на диване с газетой . или спала . она была рада , что отчим ее не трогает . все доставалось мне . про мать как нибудь отдельный пост напишу . врагу не пожелаешь такое . на фоне этого ада и унижений эти трое мужчин давали мне любовь , ласку , понимание , разговаривали со мной , советовали что-то , давали еду . ни один из них не относился ко мне плохо . тот , что на 30 лет старше даже с уважением относился , и говорил о любви . в 18 лет все это закончилось . все как-то пошли своей дорогой . умер отчим . потом я вышла замуж за замечательного человека . он меня очень любит . у меня дочь 9 лет . я стараюсь , чтобы она даже рядом с такой юностью , как у меня , не проходила . ===================== из писем в nemolchi.uz . вы можете отправить свою историю анонимно :

text:
das zweite buch samuel

kapitel 13

mich macht es extrem traurig, dass mein widersacher die sexuelle freiheit dazu missbraucht, um sich selber daran zu ergötzen. mein geschenk an dich, durch die sexualität leben weiterzugeben, ist kein spielball für abartigkeiten und perversionen. die daraus resultierenden ergebnisse wie vergewaltigungen, #metoo, erniedrigungen und mordtaten, rechtfertigen es, dir diesbezüglich klare grenzen aufzuzeigen. freude, lust und befriedigung ist dir dennoch gesichert. im gegenteil! du und dein partner erleben so nicht nur eine körperliche, sondern vor allem die emotionale und geistige befriedigung eurer echten liebe. das dein umfeld, weil habgierig und zügellos, dass nicht versteht und nachvollzieht, hält dich sicherlich nicht davon ab, meinen grundsätzen zu gehorchen. bei amnon endete seine gier im eigenen tod. die liebe zu tamar, erwies sich als reine sexuelle gier, die befriedigt, dann in hass umschlug. lass dich nicht täuschen! dein herz führt dich in die sackgasse, meine grundsätze zu deinem ziel und zu einem erfüllten sexualleben.
.
.
.
.

text:
things have been quiet on the music front for while and that is on purpose. you may have seen i was on set last week shooting my new walking through fire video, i'm 're branding and re releasing the whole thing but this time doing it right. this time getting it heard by the right people.  and following it up with a couple of other absolute bangers i've been working on.

i spend too much time worrying i'm getting too old for this. worrying it won't ever happen. but truth of the matter is, now is the time i've found myself as an artist. something i didn't have even a few years ago. walking through fire was written after a trip to the police station. in the run up to the #metoo movement. in the hopes of putting the man that caused me so much hurt behind bars forever.  it was that moment where i think i realised the artist i was and the artist i could be. i found strength that day i never thought i'd have. strength that sticks with me and strength that i hope can inspire others.  for the first time in my life i'm ready to say what ive got to say. and to me having something to say is the most important part of music

text:
no matter how much semi-autobiographical dross jonathan franzen publishes as literary fiction*, somehow romance will still always be the easiest genre to scoff at. and i get it! i used to be one of the scoffers. aside from a brief phase my big sister went through when i was 12, there were no romance novels in my book-packed house growing up. no friends in college put them in my path. i was in my 20s before i read a romance more modern than jane eyre.
🖤
for sure romance isn’t gonna be everyone’s thing, the way sci-fi isn’t, or brit lit. but the older i get the more suspicious i am of that easy dismissal. how can we tease out a lack of affinity for this wide-ranging genre from our culture’s lack of regard/downright antipathy toward women‘s voices, stories, preoccupations, gazes, & desires?
🖤
for all that i will now vocally defend the genre, i toss more of it than i read. a lot of the big names in romance are pitching a version of feminism that is constraining & frustrating to me, or just feels plain regressive. which is why i’m thrilled to have discovered alyssa cole.
🖤
“intersectional feminist romance” is the label, if you care about labels. real, 21st c., & not-fucking-around are her characters + writing. there was a moment reading duke by default when a man apologized & said he needed to do better, & i rolled my eyes like, “pffft, fantasyland.” before remembering that, duh, all fiction is a form of fantasy!! and that’s important. it’s valuable (& delicious) to be able to retreat into a world where people treat each other like equals & apologize when they don’t. it’s valuable bc you can’t manifest a world you can’t first imagine. it’s valuable bc, in the era of #metoo & a more general societal reckoning with vast gender inequities, the prospect of guys who ask permission, recognize women’s worth, aren’t perfect but can hear that they aren’t, is sexy af. if we don’t demand it in our fiction, how can we demand it in real life?
⚔️
this novel is full of tension, joy, discovery, & sword-grinding (actual & metaphorical). alyssa cole is my new bar-setter for romance, & i can’t rec her enough to lovers of the genre or skeptics willing to take a chance.

text:
⭐️ review ⭐️⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
happy friday! ❤️ thank you to @mubeatie and @amazonpublishing for the advanced copy of the forgotten hours by @katrinschumann. ⁣⁣⁣
this one is a thought-provoking and compelling story about family loyalty and the secrets we keep from ourselves. this well-crafted novel is especially important in the #metoo era. ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
it’s about the fallout of a new york family after a teen accuses her best friend’s father of sexual assault. it intertwines the now-grown daughter’s memories with her desperate search for answers. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
after a prologue, we meet katie gregory as her life is looking up: she’s working in new york city at a good job and her boyfriend is a dedicated artist. but she never can quite leave her past behind, especially now that her father who went to prison for sexual assault is now getting out. while katie was always steadfast in her loyalty for her father, now that he’s about to leave prison, details of that fateful night resurface and old memories collide with new realities.⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
the chapters alternate between the night in question and the present as katie faces the implications of her father’s reentry into her life.⁣ each of the characters are written very well and felt real, especially the protagonist katie as she’s stuck in the middle of an impossible situation. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
much of the story is about how memory isn’t always a reliable source and the impact of trauma on our recollections. it’s an interesting concept because we like to believe our memories are truth-tellers. but so much can skew what actually happened. this one will make you think.⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
there’s no question it’s hard to read about sexual abuse. but i will say, the subject matter, while difficult, is handled with compassion in this read.⁣⁣⁣⁣ the forgotten hours is available now. 📚⁣⁣⁣
.⁣⁣⁣
.⁣⁣⁣
.⁣⁣⁣
.⁣⁣⁣
.⁣⁣⁣
.⁣⁣⁣
.⁣⁣⁣

much of the story is about how memory isn’t always a reliable source and the impact of trauma on our recollections. it’s an interesting concept because we like to believe our memories are truth-tellers. but so much can skew what actually happened. this one will make you think.⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
there’s no question it’s hard to read about sexual abuse. but i will say, the subject matter, while difficult, is handled with compassion in this read.⁣⁣⁣⁣ the forgotten hours is available now. 📚⁣⁣⁣

text:
last night on shake the heavens, i taught on the power of faith as i referenced the story of the woman who had the issue of blood for twelve years.
_____
one of the things that stood out to me in that story is that after she'd touched the hem of jesus's garment, she remained in hiding. 
_____
she didn't realize that she was not only healed but she received his power!
_____
she received his power to come out of hiding and tell her story! 
_____
but something dynamic happened after she told her story! 
_____
she was then made whole!
_____
what a powerful revelation! 
_____
telling her story positioned her to be healed not just from hemorrhaging but every other place that was broken! 
_____
the woman with the issue of blood reminds me of so many of us. god has done some miraculous, powerful things on the inside of us yet we are still in hiding! 
_____
the question i pose to you today is, "are you ready to come out of hiding be made whole?" _____
you have the power within your story to be made whole! 
_____
one more thing i want to point out is that, she went from being terrified to to being able to tell her story before the crowd. that's what the power of telling your story will do. it gives you boldness and courage! 
_____
that same power is available to you. 
_____
with that being said, today is your day to operate in extraordinary faith like the woman with the issue of blood and activate the power to tell your story. 
_____
today is the last day for the early bird special for the reveal: a prophetic book writing masterclass!

text:
💐de mujer a mujer💐
las últimas noches fueron de lo más inspiradoras para mi. 
naturalmente, surgieron conversaciones con mi madre en donde nos permitimos fluir de mujer a mujer, intercambiando experiencias de toda índole.
.
en la primer charla, surgieron relatos sobre sus dos partos, la forma en la que ella los ha experimentado, que le fue de ayuda y que no. mientras tanto, yo la escuchaba maravillada y agradecida y a su vez la veía a ella radiante y plena a medida que recordaba.
.
durante la segunda charla, la de ayer, surgieron temas que tienen que ver con nuestra vulnerabilidad como mujeres en un sistema patriarcal. escuché relatos tanto de ella, como de mis abuelas y tías y también ella, escuchó algunos mios. fue hermosamente sanador poner ciertas cosas en palabras y a su vez, pude sentir cuántas memorias propias de nuestro linaje quedan por sanar. fue todo muy claro. 
de repente pude ver cuantas experiencias nos unían a todas las mujeres de la familia.
.
a su vez, pienso en mis amigas. en las mujeres que me rodean y no puedo dejar de sentir admiración, inspiración y unión. 
me maravilla saber que hoy en día, los vínculos pasan por otro lado, por un lado más amoroso y comprensivo. cuidandonos mutuamente de no juzgar, aún sabiendo que queda mucho por deconstruir, mucho por resetear. "es que son muchos años con un mismo chip".
.
por eso te pido que hables, que compartas tu sentir, que dejes de callar. que sepas que no estás sola. que cuides de ti misma, eligiendo tus vínculos, relacionandote con aquellas personas que te permiten ser quien sos con todo lo que eso implica. ya no estamos solas. nos tenemos y se siente maravillosamente bien.
.
las quiero mujeres!
.
.
.
#vulnerabilidad #yogawoman #ashtangayoga #instagood #mujerciclica

text:
big love february 😊
february and it’s holidays hasn’t been my favorite month.  and like a lot of men and women- the 14th is one of my least favorite days of the year.  single or attached the day has been full of expectations and disappointments and requests not made- 
so, let’s do something about it!  let’s make february the month to bathe ourselves in deliciousness, tasting and enjoying the sweet nectar out there
happy february- the month of soul indulgence. 
and maybe a little snarky just for fun. 
and clearing the throat chakra with that satisfying fuck for good measure 💚❤️💕🌈💗

i love life. i love myself. i love being happy again and healing

text:
black history every day. daily opportunities for white people to do more than lament the realities that cause discomfort and take action. daily opportunities for all people to celebrate african-american achievement and the invaluable consequences of more selfless undertakings than we can collectively count. during black history month and in every month that follows it: educate yourself, dismantle the workings of whiteness, contribute to the redistribution of power, and become as intersectional as fucking possible. feminism is not a white woman's movement. the driving forces behind #metoo are to support all victims of sexual assault. actions taken to deconstruct the patriarchy aren't actions for white women and allies to take alone. i consider daily that inclusivity is the only way to make progress.
.
.
.
today, a highlight on sojourner truth: in 1851, truth attended the ohio women's rights convention in akron, ohio, where she delivered her famous extemporaneous speech on women's rights, later known as "ain't i a woman." her speech demanded equal human rights for all women as well as for all blacks.
.
.
.
"that man over there says that women need to be helped into carriages, and lifted over ditches, and to have the best place everywhere. nobody helps me any best place. and ain't i a woman?" / “truth's ‘ain't i a woman’ showed the lack of recognition that black women received during this time and whose lack of recognition will continue to be seen long after her time. ‘black women, of course, were virtually invisible within the protracted campaign for woman suffrage’ as said by davis supports truth's argument that nobody gives her "any best place" but not only her but black women in general.”
.
.
.

text:
my husband works hard. especially since i'm still on a fully unplanned and unnecessary extended unpaid leave . here he is rocking our son(or was ) , rubbing spud's stomach(or was) while sleeping in such a strange uncomfortable position that he didnt plan on being in. even when l woke him up he was still trying to rock our son and rub spuds stomach.
.
he does his best at home. we're both first time parents but due to the stigmas , stereotypes and misinformation, many fathers dont know as much as us moms do. i've never had a miscarriage,  child, a younger sibling and/or babysat any children. neither has my husband yet l somehow know more than him. 85% of the stuff that l know isnt even from reading. it's just from being taught or spoken of because i'm a female.
.
fathers and mothers, please teach your sons how important it is to not only know this information but also that they need to do some reading and research. it's unfair to us females when you avoid all these types of talks with them. gay or straight, when they begin to have sisters, girl cousins and even friends who are just girls they should know how to help them in certain situations. when they have one nights, girlfriends, and wives they need to know how our bodies work, how our cycles work, how pregnancy works , how postpartum is, that they can help with feeding even while mom is ebf and so on but most importantly how to help and be there during these important times when we cant help ourselves especially since it's mostly involuntary.
🚫
stop avoiding these conversations no matter how weird or icky they are. its damaging to them and the future females in their lives.
.
my husband does the best he can with the knowledge that he does have and l cant thank him enough.
.
.
.

sit tight, grab your popcorn, and enjoy the show.

yours,

the sharpshooter

text:
"in many circles resistance has come to be glorified obscuring the conservative nature of such a stance behind a veil of radical rhetoric. resistance is seen to be all that is possible, while constructive projects are nothing but a dream. while it can be important in some circumstances, in the task of building a new world, resistance is futile."- inventing the future, @versobooks ---------------------------------------------------
"and i don’t go for this aggressive, confrontationist approach that is now being adopted in this #metoo situation...the movement seems to be becoming like that – trivial and mendacious.

this is a very serious subject, what women have gone through, not today but for centuries. i don’t think it should be allowed to lose its credibility by what is happening today...what we need is a comradeship between men and women." - #nayantarasahgal
@scroll_in
#towardsasexpositivesociety

text: "the sneaky thing about the gillette ad, released last week and addressing the very topical debate on toxic masculinity and #metoo, is that it’s hard to object to. the commercial – subtle as a mallet – features versions of average joe soul-searching in bathroom mirrors, flashing back to boys bullying each other, pinching women’s bottoms and talking over female colleagues as audio from news footage of recent #metoo coverage echoes in and out. then we’re at a barbecue as a line of fathers chant ‘boys will be boys’ (these men are wrong, stupid) before segueing into the commercial’s final movement: a world where good guys intervene in bad behaviour, and millennia of patriarchy is finally undone." read more on #gillette, and capitalism's claims on our consciences, here: https://plinth.uk.com/blogs/magazine/the-best-a-man-can-get

text: rough week for me this week. i’m hoping you’re having a great one though and that this weekend is relaxing/fun for all of us. stress is a real thing and i’m so glad that all of my troubles have taught me to reach out for help when i need it. i’ve learned a lot of great coping skills from my therapists over the years. one of my favorites is to just plain keep everything relative. i can still look at my life right now and realize i still got a job, a car, and a home to go to. i’ll be okay because i’ve got some pretty badass friends too. i’m feeling better than yesterday but i’m assuming i still have some stressful days ahead of me. i’ll be okay. i’m hella glad this weekend is here 😉. -vu❤️💜 #vaginasunitedvu

text:
this was how our next generation female leaders spent last friday with our january #mentor @iphieadizue.
.
thank you mrs. iphie chuks-adizue @iphieadizue for sharing your journey with the #ngfl.
.

some of the best takeaways from the session on personal accountability to track growth and maximize performance were:
1. discover your big why
2. say no to things that are not in line with your priorities, so that you can say yes to things that are in line with your priorities
3. you don’t have to slow down for people to catch up especially when you are not in the same race.

text:
are you using your college degree?🧐
.
yeah me either 🤣 of course i gained a ton of knowledge and a bigger worldview than i may have acquired without it but y’all the world is a changin’ and there are so many open doors with this thing called the internet and social media!
.
at first exploring a company that solely used the influence of social media as a source of income was super off-putting. in fact i thought they were all pyramid schemes and only weirdos messed with that stuff. i’m weird - but not that weird🙃
.
then one day i was sitting with my colicky baby in my arms, dreading going back to work because she wouldn’t take a bottle and kicking myself for not finding a way to stay home with her before then. i was also trying to do a very hard workout from home that my mom bladder was not even close to ready for and those baby blues were settling in.
.
then someone was brave enough to share their own experience with these home workouts, a no-brainer way to have a healthier diet each day and also a way i could begin working for myself.
.
i swallowed my pride as a former collegiate cheerleader, a university graduate and a recovering know-it-all and decided to stop giving af about what everyone else would think and just go for it.
.
and i haven’t looked back. i’ve gained much more than a pretty good #mombod in these 4 years. my sahm fund has grown, i’ve become a leader, learned business and social media practices and been able to wrap my arms around some wonderful ladies and pray they know how special they are.
.
i’m accepting another round of ladies to begin their fitness journey in my challenge group using the exact same tools i do. if you want the details drop a 💃🏼and i’ll be in touch asap!
name: G A B B Y  L A S S I T E R

text: well here it is, better late than never. finally got around to narrowing my top 5000 moments of 2018. so grateful for my light brown privilege. a lot of people tried to tell me 2018 was hell and i just had to cancel that negativity. stay positive peeps. the universe wants you to succeed. don’t let all this systemic racism, family separation at the border, attacks on reproductive rights, raging wild fires, arctic blasts, modern day lynchings, school shootings, complicated tax filings, gov shutdown, marie kondo, frye fest documentary, akwafina controversy, puerto rico is part of america, there’s no difference between climate and weather, dinosaurs and jesus walked the earth together shit get to you. just keep posing and keep them happy kids and avocado toast pics coming. 2019 is gonna be great. looking forward to watching the universe revolve around you, the people. here are some hashtags i’d like to see (continue) trending this year. #cubanmodel #greennewdeal #konmari #metoo #timesup #blm #resist #kamalaharris #cardib #puertorico #venezuelalibre #impeachtrump #yalitzaaparicio #blackpanther2 #captainmarvel #optoutside #szechuansauce #cerseilannister #powder #yewwwtah #carlinwasright #larrydavid #smokeythebear #modelswanted #croquetas #nevertoolate

tonight is our opening night!
come check me out as i perform a few pieces at the production of the "odu monologues". it's our personal rendition of #vaginamonologues. the pieces i'm performing - written by yours truly - share intimate parts of my life that most of you don't know. 👀 the show touches on sexuality, love, self empowerment, and the #metoo movement. adults only, please. come out in support! tickets are only $5. you can hit me up to get tickets (or make a donation if you can't make it) or you can pay at the door. all proceeds go to the ywca to support women and girls in norfolk. thanks in advance! 🤗
show details:
when: friday february 1st & saturday february 2nd at 7pm
where: odu university theatre  4608 hampton blvd. norfolk virginia
see you there!

text:
the hrts unscripted content group's spotlight: how to prevent sexual harassment in production was held on december 4th, 2017, at the beverly wilshire hotel. a panel of experts on production, entertainment law and employment litigation headlined a candid dinner discussion of how to create a culture of zero tolerance for sexual harassment on productions, and best practices for identifying and addressing harassment when it does occur. speakers included talya friedman and joel kelly (jackson lewis p.c.) and marjorie williams, (endemol shine north america). this event was moderated by scott hervey, (@scottmhervey) (weintraub tobin and president, hrts' unscripted content group). photo credit: @chynafotos

#flashbackfriday #hrts #ucg #spotlightdinner #entertainment #tvindustry #experts #paneldiscussion #metoo #zerotolerance
name: HRTS
tweet_full:
the hrts unscripted content group's spotlight: how to prevent sexual harassment in production was held on december 4th, 2017, at the beverly wilshire hotel. a panel of experts on production, entertainment law and employment litigation headlined a candid dinner discussion of how to create a culture of zero tolerance for sexual harassment on productions, and best practices for identifying and addressing harassment when it does occur. speakers included talya friedman and joel kelly (jackson lewis p.c.) and marjorie williams, (endemol shine north america). this event was moderated by scott hervey, (@scottmhervey) (weintraub tobin and president, hrts' unscripted content group). photo credit: @chynafotos

text:
the incest survivors resource network states that "the erotic use of a child, whether physically or emotionally, is sexual exploitation in the fullest meaning of the term, even if no bodily contact is ever made.” ———————————————————————— [he called it ‘love’ continued...]this time he was parked on the street in front of my house (my dad was out of town working) and we were in the back seat of his pickup truck.

i don’t remember everything about that night, but i do remember laying down in the back seat, making out and his hands starting to wander... again.

his hand traced along the curves of my back, but this time he didn’t stop at my butt.

his hand slid past my ass and started curling under... until he felt my pad. he froze. i froze. his hand slid back up. a quiet sigh of relief escaped my lips, but this time my face was buried in his chest.

thank god that at 15 years old i didn’t use tampons like most girls i knew. and thank god at night i used to use the huge maxi pads that felt more like a freaking diaper.

in that moment, i truly believe my period saved me. who knows what would’ve happened had it not been that time of the month or had i not been wearing a diaper sized pad. 
all i know, is that after that night i thought that as long as i was on my period, i would be ‘safe’. #sexualabuse #emotionalmanipulation #psychologicaltrauma #rapeculture #metoo

why do we need queer-inclusive sex ed? 📚💡🤔
.
"the glsen 2013 national school climate survey found that fewer than five percent of lgbt students had health classes that included positive representations of lgbt-related topics."
.
"among millenials surveyed in 2015, only 12 percent said their sex education classes covered same-sex relationships."
.
"hundreds of studies have shown that well-designed and well-implemented sex education can reduce risk behavior and support positive sexual health outcomes among teens..."
.
"for lgbtq youth to experience comparable health benefits to their non-lgbtq peers, sex education programs must be lgbtq-inclusive."
.

text:
we all see our very own reality; everything is influenced by our personal experiences.
do you know why there are so many misunderstandings? because we assume things based on our expectations; we mostly don't use our ability to think further about how others could experience our actions towards them or our environment. this happens between different genders (due to the ways we've been raised influenced by social norms) but actually more between people who have made different experiences and stand at their point of view. let me tell you, this bigotry can be extremely hurtful!
i thought for a while about this and want to start a little series of sharing some of my stories and views with you. maybe it helps some to understand things on a deeper level. without sharing a little bit of ourselves, no one will ever understand the other one - communication is key.

text: i loathe this time of year. the media trots out their annual stories dissecting the less than one second of janet's halftime show performance. it does nothing but remind me that the media played a huge role in damaging her career... wasn't just les moonves. it also does nothing but remind me of how timberlake's career just skyrocketed because the media put all the focus on janet and coddled him as some sort of victim. it's funny to me how timberlake is able to get away with using her to this day. covering her song in concert, trying to use her name to get people to watch his halftime show...as if she'd ever,  using the choreography for her song for his tribute to tina landon when he could've chosen anything else with another artist that she's done. my question is...where the hell is #metoo and #timesup ? where were they when the les moonves story came out even? i'm tired of timberlake and him continually getting a pass on this shit. #janetjackson #janetjacksonappreciationday  #apologizetojanet

text:
neue strecke entdeckt ⛰ 🌲
man läuft einfach los und und irgendwann gibt’s wenig bemerkbare abzweig rechts, kaum befahrbar und anscheinend auch nicht so oft belaufbar. zumindest heute waren da keine menschliche spuren zu sehen, nur spuren von waldbewohner 
nach der erste hälfte war es auf einmal eisdecke auf der strecke schön mit schnee ❄️ verdeckt. weil ich so fasziniert von der natur war, habe es überhaupt nicht gemerkt und als ich mir dachte- „hm 🤔irgendwie ist der griff von meinen schuhen nicht so griffig, muss ich auf passen....“ da bin ich schon mit meinem elefanten körper voll gedonnert 🙈😁
aufstehen über sich lachen und weiter ( nur linke seite hat die restliche 32 min. sich gemeldet🤦🏼‍♀️, aber was soll’s hübsch hinfallen muss auch trainiert werden 😉) noch mal zu meine strecke. die ist so schön , man kann es kaum in wörter fassen, das soll man sehen 🤩. links von dir berg hoch, rechts abgrund und unten läuft bach. auf andere seite des baches ist wieder berg hoch. mein heiß geliebter ❄️ schnee gibt gewisse etwas 🏔 und ich bringe etwas farbe rein👩🏻‍🦰
beim nächsten mal mache ich mehr bilder von meine strecke 
bleibt fit ✌🏼👱🏻‍♀️ *********************************************
я дорвалась до шикарной беговой дороги⛰🌲🌳
горы, лес , ручей и лесные жители 🤩
с одной стороны гора вверх, с другой обрыв, где-то там в самом низу течёт ручей. по ту сторону ручья опять горы вверх. мною обожаемый снежок придаёт свою особенность, я принесла собою немного цвета в дремлющий лес 👩🏻‍🦰
