text:
📖
•••
🇫🇷 coucou,
un extrait du recueil #desauteursautoeditessemobilisentcontreleharcelementderue que vous pouvez retrouver avec d’autres sur @booknode 👍
il s’agit de la nouvelle « une fille pour un soir » de sam castel 🙂
en tout, 17 nouvelles et donc 17 voix pour s’exprimer sur le harcèlement dans les lieux publics envers des femmes, des couples homosexuels, des victimes du racisme, etc.
des genres et des tons différents.
il est en vente aux formats papier et ebook 📚
un immense merci à @lmedml.alouqua qui vous propose aussi un rdv chronique + interview sur son blog chaque mardi et c’est justement au tour de sam cette semaine !
bonne nuit 💤 •••
📒 vous pouvez retrouver mes livres, les ajouter à votre pal et consulter des extraits sur les sites de lecture comme babelio, livraddict, booknode et goodreads à mon nom d’autrice s. n. lemoing 😊
🛍 ils sont disponibles gratuitement en emprunt avec amazon kindle ou à 2.99€ pour les romans et 0.99€ pour les histoires courtes au format ebook, et entre 8 et 11€ pour les versions papier 📖
•••
🇬🇧 hi,
an excerpt from a short story of the anthology about street harassment!
this novella is about a young man who accepts to dress as a woman after his sister explains she’s harassed all the time. he thinks she’s exaggerating, but he’ll soon discover how it really is!
there’s a facebook page for the book. 17 novellas have been selected, 17 voices for women, queer people, people of color, etc. who have been harassed.
good night 💤 •••
📚 if you love epic fantasy & badass female characters you can read more info about my writings in my bio. one of them has been acclaimed by 100+ literary bloggers 😊
🛍 my writings are available for free for kindle unlimited subscribers, as ebooks at 1,15$ or 0,99£, etc. & paperback for $14 👍

text:
☝ crítica a mi 5ª novela: "hola, que le he dado a 'me gusta' y que sigo siendo fan. estoy leyendo la maga y me gusta tu escritura y los detalles como mensajes y demás en códigos coloquiales que sorprenden al releerlos. gracias margarita por esos murales de literatura para poder vivir en inocencia y en sabiduría del pueblo." :) (m. m.) 🍀 👋😹👍🐩💫puedes leer artículos míos en el apartado "colaboradores" de diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: nimy novels arrive everywhere from
http://www.bubok.es/autores/bokusu
pincha el enlace en mi perfil.

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores🔞you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults ✌😘✊ todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻

puedes seguirme además en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud 🎤(otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)📲 💃

text:
happy national teen dating violence awareness month! while all domestic violence is unacceptable, this month highlights the youth due to the alarming percentage of domestic violence survivors that are 19 or younger. according to love is respect (loveisrespect.org):
👉 over the span of one year, just about 1.5 million american high school-aged kids will experience physical abuse from a partner.
👉 around a third of adolescents is a survivor of domestic abuse.
👉 10% of high school students has been intentionally harmed (physically) by a significant other. 
comment below what you wish you knew about a past relationship that could help others now! 🍋
.
.

👉 over the span of one year, just about 1.5 million american high school-aged kids will experience physical abuse from a partner.
👉 around a third of adolescents is a survivor of domestic abuse.
👉 10% of high school students has been intentionally harmed (physically) by a significan not other.

text:
☝ crítica a mi 5ª novela: "hola, que le he dado a 'me gusta' y que sigo siendo fan. estoy leyendo la maga y me gusta tu escritura y los detalles como mensajes y demás en códigos coloquiales que sorprenden al releerlos. gracias margarita por esos murales de literatura para poder vivir en inocencia y en sabiduría del pueblo." :) (m. m.) 🍀 👋😹👍🐩💫puedes leer artículos míos en el apartado "colaboradores" de diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: nimy novels arrive everywhere from
http://www.bubok.es/autores/bokusu
pincha el enlace en mi perfil.

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores🔞you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults ✌😘✊ todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻

puedes seguirme además en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud 🎤(otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)📲 💃

text:
☝ crítica a mi 5ª novela: "hola, que le he dado a 'me gusta' y que sigo siendo fan. estoy leyendo la maga y me gusta tu escritura y los detalles como mensajes y demás en códigos coloquiales que sorprenden al releerlos. gracias margarita por esos murales de literatura para poder vivir en inocencia y en sabiduría del pueblo." :) (m. m.) 🍀 👋😹👍🐩💫puedes leer artículos míos en el apartado "colaboradores" de diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: nimy novels arrive everywhere from
http://www.bubok.es/autores/bokusu
pincha el enlace en mi perfil.

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores🔞you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults ✌😘✊ todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻

puedes seguirme además en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud 🎤(otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)📲 💃

a rainbow. and not just any rainbow. a full rainbow. i know you can’t tell from this picture but it goes all the way to the ground. very rare.  it ended a block away. i almost saw the pot of gold.  this is the promise nature makes to us. that the sun will shine and the rain will finish. but we really need both the rain and the sun for a rainbow.  yes, you know this but apply it to your life. something may suck right now (if you accept the premise that rain sucks). but the sun will come out, even if you can’t see it. and then you get the rainbow. the beauty. the very rare.  #producer #filmmaker #womenempowerment #writers #sherlockholmes #cinnamon #thecollaborative #women

text:
when we talk about consent, it’s often in the context of sexual assault and/or intimate partner violence. while these are definitely conversations that we should be having, not enough people are talking about why consent matters in healthy relationships, and that’s not good. the thing is, consent affects long-term relationships on a daily basis. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
consent  between long-term partners isn’t always specifically about sex. when you share a life with someone, both of you need to be cultivating an ongoing discussion about your boundaries with exes and friends. both of you need to work toward creating a space where you feel safe expressing what you want your relationship to look like, sexually and otherwise.

when it comes to the topic of sex, there's should be zero pressure to say "yes”. you and your partner should free each other from the fear of being pushed into doing something that you might not be 100 percent onboard with. and if you're the one asking the questions, you don't have to fear being shamed or judged by your partner, because no question is off-limits. basically, when consent is the cornerstone of your relationship, there's nothing that you can't ask for in bed, because it's understood that nothing goes down in the bedroom until both of you have actively agreed to it. now that's hot.

#sexyaftersexualassault #nomeansno #yesmeansyes #consentishotassaultisnot #consentissexy #consentismandatory #feministpositivity #consentineverything #consentinmarriage #metoo #mentoo #sexeducation #endrapeculture #endrapeculturenow #endviolenceagainstwomen #endgunviolencetogether #healthyrelationships #healthyrelationshipgoals #healtyrelationshipboundaries #growtogether #consentalways #consentismandatory

text:
for decades, humans have looked up, to father god. he told us what we could and could not do. moral, sin and the promise of an afterlife made life easier and comprehendible. men worked hard to raise money for their families, while women worked hard at home. men were the ones who mattered, who had power and a voice. women were dangerous if not contained; it was eve, after all, who got us all ‘expelled’ from paradise. sexuality was a sin, when not used to make children.
.
western society has recently been shifting. religion has been replaced by capitalism. but what do we have left? the lack of a shared meaning of life and the believe that everyone can and should always do better, has left so many of us lonely, anxious and depressed. the sexual revolution has freed us, but we’re not really sure what to do with this freedom, because we were never taught so. pornography and sexual assault are a ‘manly’/‘phallic’ solution to this fear of eve, the dangerous woman who is now freeing herself from the patriarchic cage.
.
the time has come for humans to look down, to mother earth. to learn how to treat her - and with her all that she created - with respect. to stop using and abusing. to start caring, nurturing, giving back. to stop competing over the best life; to take each others’ hands instead. to start trusting, and helping others in need. to live together in peace, to treat everyone and everything around us with respect.
.
surprise your friend with a trip to nature in a little eco caravan, for example, and spend time with mother earth while respecting her and using as little of her resources as possible. (to make this text somewhat relevant to the picture 😁)
.
may compassion replace competition.
.

text: today at the chamber's 25th pinnacle awards and anniversary of our women's network, we honored professor anita hill with a lifetime achievement award. i don't even have much to say about it except that i was unexpectedly moved. i've known for months that we were honoring her and i've heard her speak before. but something about seeing her, a black woman, a pioneer, during this time of pure craziness in our country. it brought tears to my eyes. she stood up when no one else would. we love her now, but people hated her at the time. even black people because we often hate when we publicly point out the wrongdoings of a black man (yep). she started this #metoo movement before it was the "in" thing to do. so often, we do the work no one else wants to do. i felt so proud to be in her presence and proud of our organization for recognizing her greatness (@yallacece 😊). (i guess i did have something to say).

text:
day 2 🎉 sore!! i did yoga today because the sore struggle is real. falling yesterday didn’t help..my hip is feeling all my weight crashing down on it today, ouch!! .
.
i decided to weight myself this morning..as i was undressing i started thinking how i shouldn’t be weighed after 1 day. i thought “you are just setting yourself up to be disappointed” but then i remembered that i need to stay positive. i need to remember that this is a long process and something small like a number can’t set me back. if the number is something i didn’t want to see then i’ll just have to use that as fuel for my fire. .
.
so i stepped on...and i felt confident about my first day, i worked out and it was very hard, i drank my weight in water and i’m positive! the number will not faze me..and turns out i got all in my head for no reason because i lost 3 pounds. wait..what?! is all i could think! hey i’ll take it. .
. 
later in the day, i took my favorite 5 year old to the library and got some books to workout my brain..so i’m off to do just that. .
.
a little shoutout to one of the best friends a girl could wish for @sfbaseball and the more encouraging text i woke up to..it literally made my day. love you .
. 
#ptsdawareness #metoo #woke #sober #mentalhealthawareness #invisibleillness #day2 #21dayfix #imsore

text:
har precis sett klart svt dokumentärserien "vi överlevde r.kelly". känslomixen är total: enormt hat, äckel, sorg, frustration och hopp.

att sexuellt våld mot svarta tjejer/kvinnor aldrig tas på lika stort allvar som mot vita, att det finns så många människor som stöttar psykopater och pedofiler, att pengar kan köpa en fri från _allt_, att branchen och fansen fortfarande idag använder argument som att vi måste skilja på personen och artisten/musiken.... och mycket mer.

men också hoppet i att folk, trots mordhot (osv) vågar träda fram. och när en gör det kommer det oftast fler.

att branchen börjar fatta att deras streams av artisten inte bara normaliserar beteendet utan även betalar svinen så de kan fortsätta komma undan med sina brottsliga handlingar. och att inte bara kvinnor, utan även män, äntligen vågar stå upp.

frågan är bara: vilka män vågar ta ställning för svinen vi har i vårt land? varför är det alltid bara (nästan) uteslutande kvinnor som vågar ta ställning? hur många män därute vet saker om deras branchkollegor men håller käften om det? förstår ni att ni blir medskyldiga? samma regel som vi lärde oss i skolan: att de som kollar på när mobbning sker utan att ingripa är en del av mobbningen - gäller även för sexuellt våld och maktmissbruk.

på riktigt: kan någon nämna ens 10 män som de känner till som vågat ta ställning? vi tror att vi kommit långt i sverige men vi lever i en extrem tystnadskultur där män måste börja steppa upp, även när det blir jobbigt.

se dokumentärserien. finns på svtplay.

ps: men bortse från vad psykologen säger om att barn som blivit utsatta för övergrepp själva utsätter i vuxen ålder. det skulle innebära en jävla massa pedofiler och är en myt. ds

#muterkelly #timesup #metoo #tystnadtagning #närmusikentystnar #metoobackstage #deadline #blackgirlsmatter osv osv osv.

text: yesterday i stood up for a young woman who, it appeared, was being harassed. today i was chastised by the guy’s boss (a male, of course) for speaking out. he tried to make me feel foolish & defeated although he claims he understands a woman’s point of view (bullshit, obviously). i stand by my decision for saying something. “men” don’t get how uncomfortable the action is of hugging up on a woman they barely know or grabbing a woman’s hand unexpectedly. it’s ewwy & how do we kindly say stop? it doesn’t work for animals that don’t regard women’s feelings. i will continue to speak out and speak up because no one ever did for me!!! #bebrave#sexualharassment#metoo#metoomovement#menarepigs#womenempowerment#womensupportwomen#maya#mayaangelou#women#woman

text:
happy #founderfriday 🙌🏾 allow me to reintroduce myself, my name is @brittanykingpleas and i am the founder of #wosc. here are five facts you may (or may not know) about me:

1. i started women of so cal on a whim (some might call it an inspirational nudge). i went out for lunch with some pretty powerful women...and i wanted a space to brag about them and talk about what i was learning. now, it’s growing and evolving into something i didn’t imagine and i’m here for it. 
_
2. i work as an education and employment specialist at a homeless drop-in center and shelter for young adults who are experiencing or at-risk for homelessness. my work involves supporting my clients in having an excellent resume and cover letter and being a super, supportive and patient person working a long side in job searching and finding opportunities for education that are the right fit. we are always in need of volunteers, put a 🙋🏾‍♀️ below if you’re interested. 
_
3. random things: i am 27. i’ve been to kenya twice. i love kombucha, aromatherapy, new stuff for my face and all things @lushusa 
_
4.  i am a highly empathic individual. while we all can empathize, i didn't know it was a strength until i was 22 years old. i strongly feel the emotions and intent of others -- so much so that sometimes i take them on as my own.  i am constantly working on my boundaries and ways that i can best serve others and empower myself. 
_
5. i am a follower of jesus christ.  i serve on the praise team at my church. he is a faithful god and i am loved by him unconditionally. my heart as a servant leader to my community has been nurtured by my relationship with him. 
_
so, tell me about yourself?
.
.
.
.
.

text:
did you know your happy ending could be her worst nightmare? 
when she was finished with her services (aka happy ending!), did you ask her if she was there on her own will? 
does she like her job? 
did she come to america on her own or was she told a lie to get her here. 
next time you get a massage, i ask that you start to think about how you are at the root of demand and fuel sex trafficking. 
your happy ending contributes to her slavery. next time bring a translator with you & find out how she got her job in that massage parlor (illicit massage business). just a few happy thoughts for the men visiting these massage spas. #theheartofaman #metoo #stopdemand #wearblue #behervoice #keepmassagelegit #seekreallove #pornharms

text: 🎨these are the artworks i made that were shown in the gallery for the cartooning major at my high school💞 the first one is an editorial cartoon that i made using ink wash. it talks about the abuse woman go through and how it’s hard that people don’t take them seriously because they believe she’s lying or seeking attention. they think that they are over reacting or if it’s true they try to shut them up for ever speaking about what happened behind closed doors. i really enjoyed this making this artwork and so did the super attendant when she came up to me and told me that (almost collapsed right when she left).🌙 the second one is a drawing i made were it had to involve using the “line of action”. i wanted to do sth that was challenging so i decided to draw a ballerina in a pose that i’ve never tried before.💃🏼 #art #artistoninstagram #artist #ink #metoo #politicalcartoon #ballerina #dance #digitalart #painting #inkwash #sketch #drawing

text:
this year, i came to the hard realization that every single woman i knew was a victim to sexual assault and especially harassment. this song covers the idea that no matter the situation, we are not asking for it. we are not asking for you to “compliment” us as we walk down the streets. we are not asking for you to touch us because our “outfits said so.” we are asking you to respect us and to believe us. 
if i didn’t ask and if we didn’t communicate, i’m saying no. there’s nothing more to it. yes means yes. over 35% of women have experienced sexual assault around the globe and 1/6 american women will experience sexual assault in their life time. we are done being told how we can be more careful next time. it is time for the sexual predators to be held accountable. #metoo

text:
to illustrate my point let me tell you some things about me. i had a rough childhood, was on the streets by 15, and i did some questionable shit in those years, no doubt. but what i learned during that time was invaluable to me in this #metoo era:
.
1. let people know that if they fuck with you, there will be severe consequences.
.
2. strike fear into the hearts of those who would harm you. being agreeable is a skill. being crazy is a skill. being unpredictable is the greatest skill of all. learn them all because you will need them for safety.
.
3. the fastest way to evening the playing field between a 200lb man and a 105lb woman is with a weapon. #2a
.
i was raped as a child. young girls are taught to go along to get along. we are taught to look pretty and dance with strangers, even if it’s uncomfortable. we are taught that it’s unladylike to scream, and to curse, and to fight. what we aren’t taught is the power of our own voices and how to create personal boundaries. we don’t need men to protect us. we need to learn to protect ourselves. this is only half the battle.
.
emasculating young men leads to bottled up aggression. not having friendly touch will do the same. this is why i am a huge fan of contact sports, especially jiu jitsu and wrestling. it is a natural behavior expressed in male adolescents. the bullies, btw, need wrestling and contact sports the most as an outlet. don’t simply take pity on the kid getting beat up, there’s some shit going on under the hood of the bully too.
.
if you put touch-starved boys with bottled-up aggression into a world full of girls who were raised to be “ladylike” and not fight, scream, curse, and threaten your life if you violate boundaries, do you know what you’ll get? a #metoo movement.
.
this isn’t getting solved with a fucking gilette advertisement for razors. it’s like the d.a.r.e program which was ideologically supported but totally counterproductive in reality. so fathers, raise your daughters well. mothers, raise your sons well. foster self-confidence in your children and raise children who know how to create healthy boundaries and you’ll make a generation that will change the world.

text:
they say not to look her in the eye or she'll turn you to stone with that glare of hers.  but did you ever wonder why? 
one tale of medusa's transformation from the beautiful maiden of mens inspiration for desire to a terrifying monster answers the question. and perhaps not surprisingly it is a #metoo moment.  as the story goes medusa, after being brutally raped by an over ardent suitor in lust with her beauty, was taken in by athena the goddess of war. athena took pity on medusa's soul and transformed her so no man would have want to gaze upon her and repeat such violence upon her again. medusa's ability to turn all who met her gaze to stone made her a legend of the cold hearted side of the female psyche but who wouldn't be apt to look at the world with this sort of gaze after such a tragic betrayal of personal boundaries. 
after medusa's death athena ended up with her head as a gift from persus who had slain her and was continuing to use it as a weapon turning foes to stone. athena immortalized medus's head by mounting to her shield. a wise and surprisingly endearing move on part of the war goddess.

#medusa #metoo #monster #greektales #backstory #femalearchatypes

text:
back to muslim identity -  perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks  pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.” kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. “menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, “tidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,” tukasnya.[] sumber:www.muslimahnews.co

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores🔞you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults ✌😘✊ todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻

#day1 #lovingme2019 listening to motivational speeches have helped me so much in my life! i love starting my day with one. either while taking a shower, getting ready, or during my morning drive. it always makes me feel excited and like i can do anything. i hope you will feel the same way. this is one of my favorites and a go to when i need a pick me up. honestly so many are my favorites, but this was the first one that was introduced to me when i needed it most so i guess it has a certain comfort and reminder for me. what i usually do is go to youtube and search for morning motivation or motivational speeches and i just listen. if you have any favorites please share it below or send me a message, i'd love to hear it!! .
.

text:
today february 1, 2019, marks the first day of #blackhistorymonth and the #tttstaff has decided to honor a historical black north carolinian figure each day of february | •
•
for our first honoree, we have selected charlotte’s mayor @vilyesclt ! in 2017, our mayor etched her name in the history books by becoming the first black woman to be elected mayor of charlotte, nc. vi lyes, raised in columbia, sc, an alumna of unc-chapel hill is committed to building a better charlotte.  thank you for making history and being an inspiration to so many people! | @tttmediaco .

text:
this is your #triggerwarning ... i don’t know why i felt compelled to share this story, but here you go. .
.
.
.
memorial day weekend 2005 i was 19 years old and about to graduate from the art institute of dallas. against my better judgement i decided to go on a weekend river float trip to tahlequah with my then-boyfriend and some mutual friends. i had to be back in dallas 8am tuesday morning to turn in my portfolio, or i wouldn’t be able to graduate. •

memorial day weekend is the busiest weekend for all of the river floating outfits, and campsites sell out. which means there are so many rafts, kayaks and canoes on the water that some areas get congested and people cannot get through.
•

we had a great time canoeing the 12 miles down river, but as we approached our exit area the river was so congested that our canoe tipped over, and all of our belongings fell into the water, including my car keys, never to be seen again.
•

knowing that i was not supposed to be there in the first place, and panicking because i did not want to fail out of college, i knew that i had to do whatever it took to get back to dallas in time to graduate. i was too afraid to call my parents for help because i thought they would ridicule me for making bad decisions.
•

i called a locksmith, the only locksmith that was available on a holiday weekend. the guy who came out was a total creep. i was visibly upset, and for the hour and a half he spent working on my car he kept slapping me on the ass and making crude jokes. eventually he said he could not create a key for my jeep at the campsite, so he needed to go to his shop in town to make it, and he needed the person who was paying for the key to go with him. since i was the one paying, he insisted i go with him but when i asked to bring my boyfriend along, he said he only had room in his truck for one person. (i looked in his truck, and while he did have equipment in the backseat, there was plenty of room for both of us to ride with him). we were all young, dumb, and inexperienced to recognize that this was a terrible idea.
•

not knowing what to do, i got in the car by myself and went with him to his shop in town. (cont...)

☝ crítica a mi 5ª novela: "hola, que le he dado a 'me gusta' y que sigo siendo fan. estoy leyendo la maga y me gusta tu escritura y los detalles como mensajes y demás en códigos coloquiales que sorprenden al releerlos. gracias margarita por esos murales de literatura para poder vivir en inocencia y en sabiduría del pueblo." :) (m. m.) 🍀 👋😹👍🐩💫puedes leer artículos míos en el apartado "colaboradores" de diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: nimy novels arrive everywhere from

pincha el enlace en mi perfil.

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores🔞you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults ✌😘✊ todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻

puedes seguirme además en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud 🎤(otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)📲 💃

text:
a series of serious selfies because i am so tired of feeling like i live in a world that sometimes feels so fake. i'm so tired of people taking advantage of the fact that i'm nice and force it to become weakness. and i say force, because that's exactly what they do. no matter how much you try and stand your ground, they overpower you. and no matter how clear you were from the beginning and they say they understand, it's like your honesty fell on deaf ears. and their behavior becomes rationalized. and then it's either your fault or "it's just for fun". it's not fun. when you lay ground rules, they are there for a fucking reason. it's not there to be pushed to the edge and then completely jumped over. it's there because a person has fucking morals. (please don't ask. i just wanted to share what's going on in my head because it feels hard to breathe and i know some of you can relate. much love to you all and thank you for being my support ❤️)
#sorrynotsorry #truth #metoo #overit #lisaasmr #female #youtuber #selfie #snapchat #relateable #asmrtist #eyes #glasses #serious

text:
☝ crítica a mi 5ª novela: "hola, que le he dado a 'me gusta' y que sigo siendo fan. estoy leyendo la maga y me gusta tu escritura y los detalles como mensajes y demás en códigos coloquiales que sorprenden al releerlos. gracias margarita por esos murales de literatura para poder vivir en inocencia y en sabiduría del pueblo." :) (m. m.) 🍀 👋😹👍🐩💫puedes leer artículos míos en el apartado "colaboradores" de diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: nimy novels arrive everywhere from
http://www.bubok.es/autores/bokusu
pincha el enlace en mi perfil.

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores🔞you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults ✌😘✊ todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻

puedes seguirme además en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud 🎤(otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)📲 💃

text:
two months ago my upper back was so week that at 65lbs (bar included), i would struggle to get 10 consecutive reps of front squats in. 🤭 today, i hit a pr of a 3 rep max @115lbs (after reviewing my vid i could have done one or two more or added more weight---shoulda, coulda, woulda). i've been working on these for a couple of months now. generally, people can fs only about 70-85% of their bs weightt because front squats place a greater emphasis on the upper back, quads and knees to help stabilize the bar and spine.  long story short, the bigger the number, the greater the gains. keep working my friends. the payoff feels amazing! 💪  much thanks to @_jason_harbin for an incredible program.

text: ⚠️ trigger warning ⚠️ the other day, literally, i was with a new “friend”, a female, and i got a feeling of “ive been here before” the way i felt around this person was so similar to my perpetrator.. yet they are presenting themselves as female ( and non binary at times,) but still the energy was so familiar. i ignored it, because female friendship is something that i am lacking in my life right now. leaving my friends and community in the bay area was very hard, and i have not created any meaningful friends here, yet. so, my need to be spending quality time was present and i ignored a familiar feeling. but, at one point, something they did was so similar to my perpetrator that i started to get a flashback, ptsd showing up, and still i thought, “nah, im just still healing, all is good”. finally, at the end of the night, something happened that was like the universe hit me over my damn head as if to say.. look closer, that feeling you have, that’s real. essentially this person walked away from me at an event saying they’d be waiting for me outside, and when i walked outside they had left. they then blocked me on their phone. my calls wouldn’t go thru nor texts. i went into what i can only describe as a panic, an anxiety attack and onset of a ptsd. being left without explanation, with no warning, especially when nothing had prompted it and things were “fun” is my trigger point and is so painful. i sent an message via ig to see at the very least if they were ok. i woke up to a message that they felt like taking off with someone else, that they had met and “i should not tell them who to talk to that’s not cool.” this scenario was word for word what my perpetrator would do when we went out in public. and gaslight me into believing i actually caused it. bottom line- abuse is gender less, healing does not happen overnight and i am still in process. #gaslighting #narcissisticabuse #recovery #metoo #survivingdomesticviolence #domesticviolence #domesticviolenceawareness #domesticabuse #trauma #ptsd #flashback #baiting #publicabuse #cptsd #recovery #enddomesticviolence #narcissism #intuition #trustyourgut #emotionalabuse #emotionalabusesurvivor #traumarecovery #triggers

text:
for the record....”the case is brought by the state. the prosecutor is the one who decides whether to move forward in the case against the defendant. so, technically the victim has no power to drop charges against an alleged aggressor because criminal charges in most states are only brought by members of law enforcement bodies.” as if we had a choice and you give up your rights when you grab someone 70% smaller than you by the neck thrashing her to a car and cement floor. 
this whole story is spun into a custody battle to only deflect the real issues at hand then and now still. there has never been a custody battle there has been a be nice to a little kid battle. a listen to a little kid battle. validate feelings battle. -
-
-
-

text:
en días recientes me sentía muy afligida por toda la inseguridad que han vivido muchas mujeres en el #transporte de la #ciudaddeméxico, pero también en todo el país 🇲🇽 sin embargo ayer algo curó un poco esa parte que se me estaba rompiendo ♀️. y es que ayer la ciudad de méxico hizo historia al instaurar el primer parlamento de mujeres de esta capital. para empezar la sesión se seleccionó la mesa directiva integrada por norma don juan, una mujer representante de pueblos originarios de la ciudad de méxico así como por la activista trans  hazel gloria davenport, como presidenta y vicepresidenta, respectivamente. casi todas las integrantes de este parlamento portaban, ya fuera en sus muñecas o en sus cuellos, el pañuelo verde 💚 que es símbolo de protesta por un #abortolegalya seguro y gratuito para todas las mujeres y niñas. retumbó en este recinto legislativo el grito de "¡nunca más sin nosotras" ! que también fue pronunciado en náhuatl por norma don juan.

la investigadora #feminista olivia tena guerrero, a quien yo admiro, no sólo puso en alto el pañuelo verde sino que también se pronunció en la tribuna a favor de mantener la política del aborto bajo estas condiciones y preponderando siempre el estado laico. la diputada paula soto dio certezas de que en ese parlamento se iban a terminar las perspectivas del patriarcado "y si no lo hacen así
, que las mujeres de la ciudad de méxico se los demanden". y a pesar de que un partido tiene la mayoría legislativa en ésta cámara de diputados y diputadas en días ordinarios, fue sin duda este el parlamento más armonioso que se haya visto con una sola consigna: qué tiemblen los machistas porque américa latina será toda #feminista.

name: Estefanía Camacho
tweet_full:
en días recientes me sentía muy afligida por toda la inseguridad que han vivido muchas mujeres en el #transporte de la #ciudaddeméxico, pero también en todo el país 🇲🇽 sin embargo ayer algo curó un poco esa parte que se me estaba rompiendo ♀️. y es que ayer la ciudad de méxico hizo historia al instaurar el primer parlamento de mujeres de esta capital. para empezar la sesión se seleccionó la mesa directiva integrada por norma don juan, una mujer representante de pueblos originarios de la ciudad de méxico así como por la activista trans  hazel gloria davenport, como presidenta y vicepresidenta, respectivamente. casi todas las integrantes de este parlamento portaban, ya fuera en sus muñecas o en sus cuellos, el pañuelo verde 💚 que es símbolo de protesta por un #abortolegalya seguro y gratuito para todas las mujeres y niñas. retumbó en este recinto legislativo el grito de "¡nunca más sin nosotras" ! que también fue pronunciado en náhuatl por norma don juan.

la investigadora #feminista olivia tena guerrero, a quien yo admiro, no sólo puso en alto el pañuelo verde sino que también se pronunció en la tribuna a favor de mantener la política del aborto bajo estas condiciones y preponderando siempre el estado laico. la diputada paula soto dio certezas de que en ese parlamento se iban a terminar las perspectivas del patriarcado "y si no lo hacen así
, que las mujeres de la ciudad de méxico se los demanden". y a pesar de que un partido tiene la mayoría legislativa en ésta cámara de diputados y diputadas en días ordinarios, fue sin duda este el parlamento más armonioso que se haya visto con una sola consigna: qué tiemblen los machistas porque américa latina será toda #feminista.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
sometimes i just need to escape. i talked with my therapist today about how i have 25 years of daily abuse locked up in the box in my head. i get overwhelmed easily and it's hard not to let all of the memories, feelings, and all the horrible things he said and did take over. so an escape is needed. i need the break from all the crap. so i'm giving myself permission to eat food that is not on my diet, to sleep in, and to not worry about tomorrow. i guess it's self care, but since i've never done that either, i'm figuring it out as i go. the kids are out of town on business for a bit, so i've got the house to myself. it's nice and i'm taking the opportunity to try to escape, even if it's only for a little bit. i have to remember i'm starting with baby steps. 
#escape #selfcare #selflove #recover #recovery #itsgottagetbetter #metime #survivor #thrive #keepgoing #yougothis #youarenotwhathesaidyouare #domesticviolence #rapesurvivor #narcissisticabuse #narcissist #ptsdsurvivor #traumasurvivor #selfharm #suicide #mentalhealth #metoo #cutting

text:
as many of you know i am participating in the redcon1 readiness trials challenge. the week 1 challenge is our “why” for participating in the challenge. 
making this video was one of the hardest things i’ve done in a very long time. whether i win this weeks challenge or not i believe by speaking my truth it is a therapeutic step towards a mental transformation as well as a physical. 
so much goes on in this world and you never know that a person you see everyday may have been impacted by that situation that seems so distant from your everyday life. so here is my story and i hope that it will help others who have went through similar experiences continue to push on and to become the best they can be in all aspects of life. never give up on you and never give up on your dreams. #redcon1 #rc1checkin #redcon1readinesstrials2019 #lgbtq #lgbt #entrepreneur #love #fitness #challenge #videoftheday #competition #fitnessinspiration #inspiration #createdforapurpose #healthandwellness #motivation #bodybuilding  #metoo #ptsd #veteran #anxiety #panicattack #mentalhealthawareness #movement #vetlife #unapologeticallyme

text:
pictured above is my 5yr old princess. she loves sharks, horses and has a amazing imagination. she is also super competitive and loves to play sport and i love that about her. i want to always encourage her to play sports. it's ok for girls to play sports right?
. of course it is
.
i am a firm believer in girls in sports but as parents we are failing them. we dont involve them in sports as much as we do to our boys and that needs to change. it's in the early learning stage that kids fall in love with everything they will value later as an adult. if we ever want to see professional women's sports taken more serious and paid just as men's do, it starts now.
.
this is not a rant is real, i have 4 classes coming up in one day. 39 total kids and out of those 39 only 7 girls. this is not a post to shame on boys, i have a son as well. this is to show that as parents we need to get our girls involved more in sports....specially at an early age.
.
i know this is a long post but if you read the post i'd love to hear from you. ⚽️⚾️🏀🏐🏈⛳🎾🥊⛸⛷
what's your opinion of girls playing sports?
.
.
.
.
#jellybeansports #lifeofspeedy #girlscan #playlikeagirl #girlsinsports #girls #metoo #startshere #sports #youthsports

text:
big love february!

chocolate is said to open the third eye 😉
second only to orgasm and cuddling for 20 minutes chocolate is the biggest release of oxytocin- making us feel warm and fuzzy and also we learn faster 
decadent coffee- is there anything more delicious than a bulletproof coffee with chocolate collagen in the morning? @daveasprey i heart you.  every morning 
raw truth is vulnerable and real and opens the heart 
wild water has a life force in it.  you can almost feel it traveling down the mountain into my body 
sassy one liners make you snort

spontaneous adventures feel like getting away with something- a luxury no one else knows 
inappropriate thoughts keep the day light, and the more i know about you i know we hear a potential innuendo and come crashing through the door with “what she said” faster than the current administration tweeting emotional trauma 
far fetched dreams deepen a conversation and open the heart faster than a weighted blanket feels like a hug 
and moonlight- moon sister you were meant for wild. 
dance sister, dance.

el abuso nunca es culpa de la víctima y pedir ayuda no es nada de qué avergonzarse.

text: life’s not easy but it’s worth it. i’m feeling a sense of return. a reigniting sense of inspiration and a full circle back to myself, but a more mature version of myself. this version i could only find if i went through the depths and depressions of what it means to be human. expectations soar high, and they aren’t always met. and when they aren’t met we find suffering and despair. but we also find what we’re made of. it’s like the pain strips away all the layers you covered yourself with to ignore what’s really going on in your heart. i’m grateful for it all. and i’m so happy i get to feel it all. so here’s a happy pic of me and my mom. lol. xoxo happy friyay

text:
there is a quote in former fbi director james @comey’s book, ‘a higher loyalty’, that really struck a chord with me: “doubt is not weakness,” he said, “it is wisdom”.
_
this quote gave me a bit of an angels-singing, hallelujah moment, and i’ve been happily pondering it and applying it to my own personal day-to-day shit (of folding socks, etc - wait is that even a thing!?!), for months now. 
_
having the ability to see other people’s perspectives and thus broaden the ground on which you operate, is unequivocally the hallmark of good living!
_
this incredible book is a manifesto of ethics, truth and altruism. preach your principles, your sincerity and your selflessness in every aspect of your day. with your kids, with your work colleagues, with todd the extroverted barista, everyone!
_
while trump and dickheads like him are vandalising the world’s morals with their greed and their fear, ‘a higher loyalty’ is a book to lead us back to the light; a book to close the empathy deficit. 
_
@comey, is a man that understands the subtle power of emotional intelligence in leadership. thank you jim (first name basis 😂), as well as the unstoppable patrice, for giving us a first class ticket on a flight through your extraordinary lives. 
_
now back to my sock folding . . .
_

text:
sweet dreams my sleeping angel..you have been through a lot today and came out braver then i have ever seen you. i love your strength and courage..and i wish you didn't have to show them because of this.

today, pagan came forward to the school principal and her teacher about being sexually harassed by fellow classmates. she told them everything that was said and done.  i am immensely proud of her for coming forward and doing that.

little did we know the school was aware of these girls doing this to many students and has done nothing about it!  they even told us they had to ask the girls to stop inappropriately touching each other in school..thats it...they have just been asking them to stop..they haven't even notified the parents and its been going on since before christmas. 
pagan was in school a total of 9 days in january(thank you mother nature) and these girls did enough emotional distress that pagan became a different child at home.  she shut herself off from everyone and stayed in her room, refused to go anywhere..even places she had fun and loved going to. she stopped doing things she loved doing..like play roblox or minecraft..she just sat in her room and played with her dolls or her stuffies all of the time.

so..pagan is back to being homeschooled and the healing process is beginning.  she broke down tonight.. like she has since this started..but tonight she thanked me for being there and always believing in her. (times like this i am happy i taught her about the #metoo movement and how some people abuse it but when something does happen its ok to stand up for yourself and report it)

sexual harassment of any kind and at any age is not acceptable!

text:
“we may not hear the voices of the women who make our clothes but every garment we wear has a silent #metoo woven into its seams”. “ @carrysomers “ .
مدتی پیش هشتکی جهانی به راه افتاد که ترجمش می شه "من هم". زنان از همه ی نقاط جهان که در برهه ای از زندگی دچار آزار و اذیت جنسی شده بودن با این هشتک همدردیشون رو با هم ابراز می کردن و با شجاعت می گفتن که دچار آزار جنسی شدن و خواستار جامعه ای امن برای زنان بودن. این حرکت حتی به هالیوود هم کشیده شد و برای خیلی از مردان هالیوود رسوایی های بزرگی به بار آورد. جمله بالا از کری سومر یکی از بنیانگذاران "تحول در مد" می گه : "شاید ما صدای زنانی که لباسهایمان را دوختند را نشنویم ولی هر لباسی که ما می پوشیم یک آوای خاموش از "من هم" در خودش داره که در تار و پود لباس دوخته شده ".
هر لباسی که تن ماست داستانی از آزار جنسی به زنی است که اون لباس و برامون دوخته. بیش از 80% کارگرانی که در کار تولید لباس در جهان مشغول اند، زن هستند.
 #notofastfashion #carrysomers #metoo #feminist #feminism #yoga #يوگاايران  #نه_به_فستفشن  #نه_به_مصرف_گرایی  #آزارجنسی

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text_retweet:
#repost @penguinteen
• • • • •

bestselling author laurie halse anderson is known for the unflinching way she writes about, and advocates for, survivors of sexual assault. now, inspired by her fans and enraged by how little in our culture has changed since her groundbreaking novelspeak was first published twenty years ago, she has written a poetry memoir that is as vulnerable as it is rallying, as timely as it is timeless. in free verse, anderson shares reflections, rants, and calls to action woven between deeply personal stories from her life that she's never written about before. searing and soul-searching, this important memoir is a denouncement of our society's failures and a love letter to all the people with the courage to say #metoo and #timesup, whether aloud, online, or only in their own hearts. shout speaks truth to power in a loud, clear voice-- and once you hear it, it is impossible to ignore.
#penguin #penguinteenshowcase

a news article in sep 27, 2017 about the rape culture in japan. part 2/2

surviving sexual assault in japan, then victimized again
by megha wadhwa and ben stubbings
special to the japan times

quote: until women can approach the police after cases of sexual assault with confidence that their stories will be heard and action taken, japan’s fabled safety will always come with a caveat.

for full news article:

text:
trigger warning: rape

a news article in sep 27, 2017 about the rape culture in japan. part 1/2

surviving sexual assault in japan, then victimized again
by megha wadhwa and ben stubbings
special to the japan times

quote: however, the japanese government’s own figures show that more than 95 percent of rapes are not reported to the police. until july 2017, japan’s legal definition of rape also excluded anal or oral penetration, meaning many female victims of these kinds of attacks — and all male victims — were counted as victims of indecent assault rather than rape.

for full news article:
https://www.japantimes.co.jp/community/2017/09/27/issues/surviving-sexual-assault-japan-victimized/
